criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  (1) diagnosis of fibromyalgia, according to the American College of Rheumatology
             criteria;

          -  (2) been diagnosed for at least three months;

          -  (3) be female;

          -  (4) be in the age group between 25 and 60 years of age; and

          -  (5) sign the consent form.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  (1) cognitive deficit, evaluated through the Mini Mental State Examination (MMSE);

          -  (2) illiterate;

          -  (3) people with metallic implants located on the head, cochlear implants and cardiac
             pacemaker;

          -  (4) history of convulsion;

          -  (5) severe depression, measured by score greater than 36 on Beck Depression Inventory;
             and

          -  (6) be pregnant.
